Gradient Boosting / ML Ensembling

Ensemble ML models—including Random Forest, Gradient Boosting, and others—are widely applied to unemployment forecasting with increases in accuracy over traditional methods:

A supervised ML study compared SVM, Random Forest, Gradient Boosting, and Extreme Learning Machine in state-level unemployment rate prediction, utilizing these for improved accuracy.
ACM Transactions
RJPN Research Journal

Recent research compared ML methods directly on monthly U.S. unemployment data:

A 2025 study evaluated Random Forest, XGBoost, CatBoost, and others against standard regression models to produce timely unemployment forecasts.
arXiv
